# Booking workflow — agent reference

This rule is the single source of truth for the **new booking lifecycle** described in `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` (plan) and `docs/NEW FLOW.md` (original spec).

Whenever a task touches **booking state, emails, calendar events, sheet rows, PDF persistence, or the admin dashboard**, start here.

## 1. Status enum (canonical)

Use the string literals below in DB, code, and UI. **Postgres storage:** `TEXT` + `CHECK (status IN (...))` — see `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 **Q1.3** (avoid Postgres `ENUM` churn). Keep a single source (`supabase/functions/_shared/statusMachine.ts` on the server, `ui/src/features/admin/lib/workflow.ts` on the client — keep in sync).

```
PENDING_REVIEW
PENDING_DOCUMENTS
PENDING_GAF
PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST
PENDING_PET_REQUEST
READY_FOR_CHECKIN
READY_FOR_CHECKOUT
PENDING_SD_REFUND
COMPLETED
CANCELLED
```

> Legacy DB rows have `status = 'booked'` (or `'canceled'`). The migration maps them per **`docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q1.1**: check-in **before today (Asia/Manila)** → `COMPLETED`; check-in **today or future** → `PENDING_REVIEW`; canceled rows → `CANCELLED`.

## 2. Allowed transitions

### 2.1 Primary workflow (happy path + cancel)

```
PENDING_REVIEW              → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | CANCELLED
PENDING_DOCUMENTS           → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
PENDING_GAF                 → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST     → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
PENDING_PET_REQUEST         → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
READY_FOR_CHECKIN           → READY_FOR_CHECKOUT | CANCELLED
READY_FOR_CHECKOUT          → PENDING_SD_REFUND | CANCELLED
PENDING_SD_REFUND           → COMPLETED | CANCELLED
COMPLETED                   → (terminal)
CANCELLED                   → (terminal)
```

### 2.2 Admin-only exceptional transitions

These exist so humans can recover when automation lags, guest data changes late, or the admin needs to step the booking back one stage to redo a step.

**Forward-only override** (force-advance, e.g. when the Gmail listener / cron is skipped):

```
PENDING_GAF             → READY_FOR_CHECKIN   # approved GAF uploaded manually, no parking/pet sub-stages
READY_FOR_CHECKIN       → PENDING_SD_REFUND   # skip guest SD form stage (manual); no SD form email on this edge
```

**Backward overrides** (one-step-back recovery — the WorkflowPanel surfaces these as a "Back to …" button):

```
PENDING_DOCUMENTS           → PENDING_REVIEW
PENDING_GAF                 → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | PENDING_REVIEW
PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST     → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | PENDING_REVIEW
PENDING_PET_REQUEST         → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | PENDING_REVIEW
READY_FOR_CHECKIN           → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | PENDING_PET_REQUEST | PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST | PENDING_GAF | PENDING_REVIEW | PENDING_SD_REFUND
READY_FOR_CHECKOUT          → READY_FOR_CHECKIN
PENDING_SD_REFUND           → READY_FOR_CHECKOUT
```

The override **graph** is permissive — it lists every back-step that is structurally valid. The **UI** narrows it down via `bookingPipeline()` to a single "Back to …" button that always points at the booking's _immediately previous_ applicable step (e.g. parking is skipped when `need_parking = false`).

**Email safety:** backward transitions never fire outbound email. The orchestrator sends the ready-for-check-in email only on **forward** moves to `READY_FOR_CHECKIN` from `PENDING_DOCUMENTS` (parent docs complete) or legacy `PENDING_GAF` / `PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST` / `PENDING_PET_REQUEST` — not from e.g. `PENDING_SD_REFUND` → `READY_FOR_CHECKIN`. The `Send Ready-for-Check-in Email` dev control is shown for those same pre-ready statuses. The **SD refund form request** email is gated on `fromStatus === READY_FOR_CHECKIN && toStatus === READY_FOR_CHECKOUT` (and the `sendSdRefundFormEmail` dev control), so stepping back from `READY_FOR_CHECKOUT` to `READY_FOR_CHECKIN` does not re-send; admins can re-send from **Automation Triggers** while the booking stays on `READY_FOR_CHECKOUT`.

**Manual "force advance"** (workflow panel): admins must be able to trigger transitions that would normally be fired by **cron** or the **Gmail listener** when those automations are late or skipped.

Implementation rule: keep **two layers** in `statusMachine.ts`:

1. `canTransition(from, to)` — strict graph for automation + normal admin clicks.
2. `canManualForceTransition(from, to, ctx)` — **small explicit allow-list** of extra edges (e.g. `READY_FOR_CHECKIN → PENDING_SD_REFUND` even before cron, `PENDING_GAF → READY_FOR_CHECKIN` when the approved PDF was uploaded manually, etc.). **Never** accept arbitrary `{ toStatus }` from the client without this second check.

`transition-booking` always calls the orchestrator with `{ manual: true | false }` so the server can tell which validator ran.

The server **must** validate every transition before writing. **Manual advances** and **cron/listener** calls must all go through `workflowOrchestrator.transition()` — never duplicate side-effect logic in callers.

### 2.3 Guest-field edit → revert to review

Only revert `status` back to `PENDING_REVIEW` when both are true:

1. The update came from one of these flows:
   - Public guest update (`/form?bookingId=...`)
   - Admin booking-detail save (`/bookings/:bookingId` edit form → `guest_submissions` patch)
   - Admin guest-document replacement (`upload-booking-asset` for `payment_receipt` | `valid_id` | `pet_vaccination` | `pet_image` only — other asset types do not revert)
2. At least one workflow-sensitive field changed:
   - Facebook / Airbnb Name
   - Primary Guest name
   - Email
   - Phone Number
   - Additional Guest Names
   - Check-in and Check-out Date
   - Check-in and Check-out Time
   - Parking Details
   - Surprise decor request (`guest_requests_surprise_decor`)
   - Pet Details
   - Downpayment receipt
   - Valid ID
   - Pet vaccination and pet photo

If only non-listed fields are updated, keep the current status (do **not** revert).

When a listed field changes while the booking’s `status` is one of **`PENDING_DOCUMENTS`**, **`PENDING_GAF`**, **`PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST`**, **`PENDING_PET_REQUEST`**, or **`READY_FOR_CHECKIN`**, set `status` to `PENDING_REVIEW` (and update `status_updated_at`). In the **same write**, apply **`statusMachine.ts#pendingDocumentsClearPatchForGuestEditRevert`**: nested completion timestamps, manual-incomplete flags, approved + request PDF URLs, **admin parking settlement** columns, and **guest balance settlement** columns — **pricing snapshot fields** (`booking_rate`, `down_payment`, `balance`, `security_deposit`, `pet_fee`, `parking_rate_guest`, `guest_additional_fee`) are **not** cleared so the Pending Review pricing card persists. **`workflowOrchestrator.ts`** merges the **same patch** at the start of **`PENDING_REVIEW → PENDING_DOCUMENTS | PENDING_GAF`** before payload pricing, preventing stale `*_completed_at` from showing substeps as complete immediately after **Proceed to Pending Documents** without wiping stored pricing unless the payload supplies new values. Do **not** apply this revert when status is already **`PENDING_REVIEW`**, in **`READY_FOR_CHECKOUT`** / **`PENDING_SD_REFUND`**, **`COMPLETED`**, or **`CANCELLED`**. Fan-out (calendar color/title, sheet status column) follows the **new** status. Server helper: `statusMachine.ts#shouldRevertGuestFieldEditsToPendingReview`.

**Dev-control checkboxes** on the guest form (save DB, storage, calendar, sheet) still apply to **every** submit/save — reverting status never bypasses them. **PDF generation** is not part of guest submit; it runs from the **admin workflow** dev control `generatePdf` on `PENDING_REVIEW` → initial documents (see `admin-auth.mdc` §5).

