Rules:

- **Never CC the guest** on the GAF-request and pet-request emails to Azure.
- **The guest acknowledgement email** (to guest) is separate and only goes out on `PENDING_REVIEW → PENDING_GAF` or **`PENDING_REVIEW → PENDING_DOCUMENTS`** (same bundle as GAF request / pet / parking).
- The **parking broadcast email** uses BCC to all addresses in `PARKING_OWNER_EMAILS` (comma-separated env var; initial seed list documented in `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q4.1).
- **Parking owner replies** are **manual** in v1 — no Gmail listener for parking threads.
- **Parking nested completion:** `parking_endorsement_url` (upload) alone does **not** mark the parking sub-step complete in the admin stepper or in `PENDING_DOCUMENTS` calendar prefixes. **`parking_completed_at`** is set only when the admin confirms **Mark as Complete — Pending Parking Request** (`document_completion_target: 'PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST'` on `transition-booking`).
- **Late parking (RFCI+):** When **`need_parking`** is added or still incomplete at **`READY_FOR_CHECKIN`** or later, the **Pending Parking Request** nested sub-step stays **clickable** in the stepper (unless already complete). Admin marks complete via same-status `transition-booking` (`toStatus` = current status, `document_completion_target: 'PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST'`) — **no** revert to **`PENDING_DOCUMENTS`**.
- **Mark nested docs incomplete:** `PENDING_DOCUMENTS` → same status with **`document_completion_clear_target`** (admin-only) clears **`parking_completed_at`** or sets **`gaf_manual_incomplete` / `pet_manual_incomplete`** plus clears **`gaf_completed_at` / `pet_completed_at`** so GAF/pet show incomplete without deleting **`approved_*_pdf_url`**. **`gmail-listener`** (new approval) and **`document_completion_target`** clear the manual-incomplete flags when completing again.
- **`gmail-listener` reconciliation:** each poll, after history processing, re-runs **`WorkflowOrchestrator`** for **`PENDING_DOCUMENTS`** rows that still have **`approved_gaf_pdf_url` / `approved_pet_pdf_url`** but **`gaf_manual_incomplete` / `pet_manual_incomplete`** is true — so “Run Gmail poll” can restore completion without a new email (the original message stays in **`processed_emails`**).

## 4. Calendar color + title map

Implement once in `_shared/calendarService.ts`; the orchestrator passes the target status.

**No square brackets around status labels in production.** Full Google Calendar `summary`:

`{STATUS LABEL} - {pax}pax {nights}night(s) - {guestFacebookName}`

`statusMachine.ts#buildCalendarSummary` may prefix the summary with **space-separated** leading icons when the booking row is present: **`🎉`** if **`guest_requests_surprise_decor`**, **`🐶`** if **`has_pets`**, **`🚗`** if **`need_parking`** (each independent; order is decor → pet → parking). The event **description** (HTML) includes **Surprise decor setup: Yes/No** under **Additional Information** (`calendarService.ts`); orchestrator PATCH refreshes `description` together with `summary` when the booking row is available.

Example: `PENDING REVIEW - 2pax 2nights - Kyle Soriano`

Example (decor + pet + parking): `🎉 🐶 🚗 PENDING REVIEW - 2pax 2nights - Kyle Soriano`

Example (pet only): `🐶 PENDING REVIEW - 2pax 2nights - Kyle Soriano`

| Status                  | `colorId` | `STATUS LABEL` (first segment of `summary`)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| ----------------------- | --------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| PENDING_REVIEW          | `11`      | `PENDING REVIEW`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
