## 6. Invariants (tests should cover these)

- `submit-form` never calls Azure GAF `sendEmail`, `sendPetEmail`, `CalendarService`, `SheetsService`, or **`generatePDF`** / **`generatePetPDF`** (no guest-submit PDFs). After a successful **DB** save, when the **`sendEmail` query param is not `false`**, it calls **`sendNewBookingRequestNotify`** (owner/ops alert to **`EMAIL_REPLY_TO` only** via `new-booking-request.html`) — not workflow acknowledgement / GAF / pet / parking.
- After a successful admin **`BookingEditForm`** save (`useUpdateBooking`), the SPA calls **`sync-booking-integrations`** so Google Calendar and the Sheet row match the patched `guest_submissions` row (no workflow emails, no orchestrator).
- Only `workflowOrchestrator.transition()` mutates `status` and `status_updated_at` for **workflow transitions** (admin/cron/listener). **Exception — pipeline / `READY_FOR_CHECKIN` → `PENDING_REVIEW` safety revert** (no orchestrator): `submit-form` when workflow-sensitive guest fields change while `shouldRevertGuestFieldEditsToPendingReview(status)`, admin `guest_submissions` patch from `BookingEditForm` under the same rule, and `upload-booking-asset` for guest doc `assetType`s `payment_receipt` | `valid_id` | `pet_vaccination` | `pet_image`. These paths set `status`, `status_updated_at`, and **`pendingDocumentsClearPatchForGuestEditRevert()`** fields in one row update; they do not send workflow emails or call the orchestrator.
- `get-booked-dates` returns everything where `status <> 'CANCELLED'` (not just `'booked'`).
- Calendar event summary always matches `status → colorId` map; drift means orchestration is broken.
- Gmail listener processes every `message.id` **at most once** (idempotency via `processed_emails` table).
- Guest SD refund submissions use **`submit-sd-form`** → `WorkflowOrchestrator.transition()` (same invariants as admin transitions); **`get-sd-form`** is read-only and returns **404** unless status is `READY_FOR_CHECKOUT` **or** `READY_FOR_CHECKIN` with `sd_refund_form_emailed_at` set (returns `awaiting_balance_settlement` until status advances).

## 7. Don'ts

- Don't re-introduce `?testing=true` or a separate test-booking pipeline in UI or edge code (use staging/local Supabase instead).
- After the migration ships, **application code** should treat `status` as the **new canonical literals only**. The migration itself may still read legacy `'booked'` / `'canceled'` — that's OK, but delete dead branches once backfill is done.
- Don't put calendar/sheet/email calls inside `DatabaseService`; keep services single-responsibility.
- Don't add side effects inline to transition endpoints — go through the orchestrator so every caller (UI, Gmail listener, cron) behaves identically.
- Don't forget to update `docs/PROJECT.md` and `docs/TODOS.md` per `documentation-maintenance.mdc`.

